<br>
Severina was now 17, and already a shaman of rising power. Her service to The Tribunal was being noticed, and the quests she performed and completed only added to her growing ability. However, she still remembered her mother's instructions from years ago:<br>
<br>
Find the truth, and let it be known to all.<br>
<br>
Slowly she began poking around in what served as a library in Halas (books really aren't a Northman's idea of entertainment), and asking questions that seemingly served no real purpose, yet gave a faint glimmer of an idea. She followed up on each and every one of these leads, but to no avail.<br>
<br>
Until she talked to one of the newest merchants in Halas, Becka McGuzzler. After having helped Becka unload some crates of supplies brought from Erudin, Becka let slip a vague reference to a person that seemed to slip in and out of the shadows, and whose very form seemed to change. Severina mentally noted this, and made like she heard nothing.<br>
<br>
That night, however, she slipped outside the walls of Halas and began looking around cautiously, the ring given to her by a friend providing her with night vision. For hours she searched, looking for tracks, or some other unexplained phenomenon.<br>
<br>
This day, however, she drew a blank.<br>
<br>
However, that doesn't mean that someone wasn't there... <p><font color="red"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=46795" target="_blank">Xarien Somberstar</a><BR>
