The hidden person took note of who it was that was attempting to track him, where she came from, who she answered to... then left as quietly as she came.<br>
<br>
Severina, meanwhile, went back into Halas, trying to observe anything unusual from the cloak of invisibility. For days she kept trying, all without success. With a sigh, she headed back to her books, and her studies.<br>
<br>
In the library, the shadows moved to watch her.<br>
<br>
More days of research and observation followed, all of them drawing a blank. Her leads were getting fewer and farther between, and ending in dead ends more rapidly. Even the regular townsfolk, from O`Danos to Rose McDowell, were growing more and more silent each day, as though her searching was becoming obvious...<br>
<br>
...or, she thought, they were being told to stay silent. And who, amongst all of Halas, would not only have the ability to say something to that effect, but to enforce it?<br>
<br>
