<br>
And Barbarians aren't known for subtlety.<br>
<br>
So she'd have to keep doing what she was doing, in being as discreet as possible. Patrol patterns of the guards gave no clues, nor did invisibly eavesdropping on merchants. Silent frustration began to mount as her investigation began to wind down, with no leads and no evidence.<br>
<br>
All the while, the person that watched her since the first day kept to the shadows, except for rare occasions when things like food were needed. However, that's what the illusory arts were for. Which is fortunate that the safe spots were known, else things could be a little more interesting.<br>
<br>
