<br>
Then one day, during a blinding snowstorm, she caught a break.<br>
<br>
A gloved hand stuck out of the snow that had piled in drifts in Everfrost Peaks. Approaching it, she saw that it belonged to a Teir`Dal. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> What was one doing so far from home?</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> she wondered. Carefully clearing the snow away, she saw it belonged to a warrior-type. Inspecting closer, she saw a locket around his neck.<br>
<br>
A pulse!<br>
<br>
Mortal enemies be damned, she had enough conscience to do something. Putting him over her shoulder, she dropped a shroud of invisibility over the two of them, and carried him to an igloo, rudely evicting the goblin tenant of it with the blunt end of her staff. Setting him down, she began to chant a healing mantra, in hope of reviving him.<br>
<br>
She felt a touch on her ankle, an intense pain... then all went black. <p><font color="red"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=46795" target="_blank">Xarien Somberstar</a><BR>
